The Visual Arts Pathway program of study is designed to prepare students who wish to pursue an associates and/ or bachelor’s degree in Fine Arts after graduating from MACCS. Courses offered are designed to acquaint students with fundamentals of visual arts including painting & drawing, photography, 3D design, mixed media, the history of art, as well as the important role which art plays in society.

Here is photograph by Sean Hinzman, Freshmen, who won Honorable Mention with Future Voices of NM. Join MACCS for the 2020-21 school year at nmmediaarts.org/apply

Have you thought about your future after high school? MACCS offers a vibrant Dual Credit program allowing students to earn college credits from CNM or UNM while in high school. The tuition and books for the Dual Credit classes are free to students and every student at MACCS will take at least one dual credit class. The Class of 2020 averaged 5-6 classes each!

If you're interested in learning more and think MACCS is the place for you to start your future, visit our website, nmmediaarts.org/apply and apply for the 2020-21 school year.

Our Film Production Career Pathway is designed to prepare students to enter the growing film industry in New Mexico. Classes begin as early as middle school and involve internships with local industry partners.

Courses are designed to acquaint students with the major components of film production with emphasis on the IATSE supported skills such as gripping, electrical, lighting, camera, sound design, editing and special effects.

Join the MACCS Film Production Crew at nmmediaarts.org/apply for the 2020-21 school year!

post_text:
ALL NM SCHOOLS CLOSED DUE TO CORONAVIRUS

MACCS will be closed for three weeks beginning Monday, March 16, in response to the ongoing international coronavirus pandemic.

The closure of all New Mexico public schools was ordered by Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham, the New Mexico Public Education Department, and the New Mexico Department of Health.

MACCS students do not have school on Friday, March 13, due to Parent/ Teacher Conferences. Students are scheduled to return to school on Monday, April 6, after Spring Break. MACCS will continue to provide updates as information becomes available.
